<div class="markdown"><h1>Intro to Analyzing RV Timeseries</h1><h4>Astro 589: Week 4</h4></div>





<div class="markdown"><h1>Circular RV Model</h1><p>Velocity of Planet: </p><p class="tex">$$v_{pl} = 2\pi a_{pl} / P$$</p><p class="tex">$$a = a_{pl} + a_\star$$</p><p>Velocity of Star:   </p><p class="tex">$$M_\star v_\star = m_{pl} v_{pl}$$</p><p class="tex">$$v_\star = \frac{m_{pl}}{M_\star+m_{pl}} \frac{2\pi a}{P}$$</p><p>Doppler effective is only sensitive to motion projected onto observer's line of sight</p><p class="tex">$$RV_{\star} = \frac{m_{pl}}{M_\star+m_{pl}} \frac{2\pi a}{P} \sin i$$</p></div>


<div class="markdown"><h1>Keplerian Orbit</h1><img controls="" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/eb/Orbit1.svg/1137px-Orbit1.svg.png" type="image/png"/><p>Credit: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/User:Lasunncty">Lasunncty</a> via <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Orbit1.svg">Wikipedia</a> (<a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/deed.en">CC BY-SA 3.0</a> license)</p></div>


<div class="markdown"><h2>Keplerian RV Model</h2><p class="tex">$$\Delta RV(t) = \frac{K}{\sqrt{1-e^2}} \left[\cos(\omega+ν(t)) + e \cos(\omega) \right]$$</p><p class="tex">$$\begin{eqnarray}
K &amp; = &amp; \frac{2\pi a \sin i}{P} \frac{m_{pl}}{M_\star+m_{pl}} \\
%  &amp; = &amp; \frac{2\pi a \sin i}{P} \\
\end{eqnarray}$$</p><p class="tex">$$\tan\left(\frac{\nu(t)}{2}\right) = \sqrt{\frac{1+e}{1-e}} \tan\left(\frac{E(t)}{2}\right)$$</p><ul><li><p>Mean anomaly (<span class="tex">\(M(t)\)</span>) increases linear with time</p></li><li><p>Eccentric anomaly (<span class="tex">\(E(t)\)</span>) specifies position in orbit using angle from center of elipse </p></li><li><p>True anomaly (<span class="tex">\(\nu(t)\)</span> or <span class="tex">\(f(t)\)</span> or <span class="tex">\(T(t)\)</span>) specifies position in orbit using angle from focus of ellipse</p></li></ul></div>


<div class="markdown"><img controls="" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/72/Eccentric_and_True_Anomaly.svg/1229px-Eccentric_and_True_Anomaly.svg.png" type="image/png"/><p>Credit: <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/User:CheCheDaWaff">CheCheDaWaff</a> via <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Eccentric_and_True_Anomaly.svg">Wikipedia</a> (<a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/deed.en">CC BY-SA 4.0</a> license)</p></div>


<div class="markdown"><h3>Keplerian Orbit in Time</h3><p class="tex">$$M(t) = \frac{2π t}{P} + M_0$$</p><h4>Kepler Equation</h4><p class="tex">$$M(t) = E(t) - e \sin(E(t))$$</p></div>


<div class="markdown"><p>No closed form solution for <span class="tex">\(E\)</span>, so solve for <span class="tex">\(E(t)\)</span> iteratively  (see <a href="#690205fb-0b95-4614-9b66-dec362ed693c">code for <code>calc_ecc_anom(M, e)</code></a></p></div>

<div class="markdown"><h2>Keplerian Radial Velocity Model Code</h2></div>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>begin 
    """ Calculate RV from t, P, K, e, ω and M0	"""
    function calc_rv_keplerian end 
    #calc_rv(t, p::Vector) = calc_rv(t, p[1],p[2],p[3],p[4],p[5])
    calc_rv_keplerian(t, p::Vector) = calc_rv_keplerian(t, p...)
    function calc_rv_keplerian(t, P,K,e,ω,M0) 
        mean_anom = t*2π/P-M0
        ecc_anom = calc_ecc_anom(mean_anom,e)
        true_anom = calc_true_anom(ecc_anom,e)
        rv = K/sqrt((1-e)*(1+e))*(cos(ω+true_anom)+e*cos(ω))
    end
end</code></pre>
<pre class="code-output documenter-example-output" id="var-calc_rv_keplerian">calc_rv_keplerian (generic function with 2 methods)</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>function calc_true_anom(ecc_anom::Real, e::Real)
    true_anom = 2*atan(sqrt((1+e)/(1-e))*tan(ecc_anom/2))
end</code></pre>
<pre class="code-output documenter-example-output" id="var-calc_true_anom">calc_true_anom (generic function with 1 method)</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>begin
    calc_ecc_anom_cell_id = PlutoRunner.currently_running_cell_id[] |&gt; string
    calc_ecc_anom_url = "#$(calc_ecc_anom_cell_id)"
    """
       calc_ecc_anom( mean_anomaly, eccentricity )
       calc_ecc_anom( param::Vector )
    
    Estimates eccentric anomaly for given 'mean_anomaly' and 'eccentricity'.
    If passed a parameter vector, param[1] = mean_anomaly and param[2] = eccentricity. 
    
    Optional parameter `tol` specifies tolerance (default 1e-8)
    """
    function calc_ecc_anom end
    
    function calc_ecc_anom(mean_anom::Real, ecc::Real; tol::Real = 1.0e-8)
      	if !(0 &lt;= ecc &lt;= 1.0)
            println("mean_anom = ",mean_anom,"  ecc = ",ecc)
        end
        @assert 0 &lt;= ecc &lt;= 1.0
        @assert 1e-16 &lt;= tol &lt; 1
      	M = rem2pi(mean_anom,RoundNearest)
        E = ecc_anom_init_guess_danby(M,ecc)
        local E_old
        max_its_laguerre = 200
        for i in 1:max_its_laguerre
           E_old = E
           E = update_ecc_anom_laguerre(E_old, M, ecc)
           if abs(E-E_old) &lt; tol break end
        end
        return E
    end
    
    function calc_ecc_anom(param::Vector; tol::Real = 1.0e-8)
        @assert length(param) == 2
        calc_ecc_anom(param[1], param[2], tol=tol)
    end;
end</code></pre>
<pre class="code-output documenter-example-output" id="var-calc_ecc_anom_url">calc_ecc_anom (generic function with 2 methods)</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>"""
   ecc_anom_init_guess_danby(mean_anomaly, eccentricity)

Returns initial guess for the eccentric anomaly for use by itterative solvers of Kepler's equation for bound orbits.  

Based on "The Solution of Kepler's Equations - Part Three"
Danby, J. M. A. (1987) Journal: Celestial Mechanics, Volume 40, Issue 3-4, pp. 303-312 (1987CeMec..40..303D)
"""
function ecc_anom_init_guess_danby(M::Real, ecc::Real)
    @assert -2π&lt;= M &lt;= 2π
    @assert 0 &lt;= ecc &lt;= 1.0
    if  M &lt; zero(M)
        M += 2π
    end
    E = (M&lt;π) ? M + 0.85*ecc : M - 0.85*ecc
end;</code></pre>


<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>"""
   update_ecc_anom_laguerre(eccentric_anomaly_guess, mean_anomaly, eccentricity)

Update the current guess for solution to Kepler's equation
  
Based on "An Improved Algorithm due to Laguerre for the Solution of Kepler's Equation"
   Conway, B. A.  (1986) Celestial Mechanics, Volume 39, Issue 2, pp.199-211 (1986CeMec..39..199C)
"""
function update_ecc_anom_laguerre(E::Real, M::Real, ecc::Real)
  #es = ecc*sin(E)
  #ec = ecc*cos(E)
  (es, ec) = ecc .* sincos(E)  # Does combining them provide any speed benefit?
  F = (E-es)-M
  Fp = one(M)-ec
  Fpp = es
  n = 5
  root = sqrt(abs((n-1)*((n-1)*Fp*Fp-n*F*Fpp)))
  denom = Fp&gt;zero(E) ? Fp+root : Fp-root
  return E-n*F/denom
end;</code></pre>

    """ Calculate RV from t, P1, K1, e1, ω1, M01, P2, K2, e2, ω2, M02 and C"""

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>""" Calculate RV from t, P, K, e, ω, M0	and C with optional slope and t_mean"""
function model_1pl(t, P, K, e, ω, M, C; slope=0.0, t_mean = 0.0)
    calc_rv_keplerian(t-t_mean,P,K,e,ω,M) + C + slope * (t-t_mean)
end</code></pre>


<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>""" Calculate RV from t, P1, K1, e1, ω1, M01, P2, K2, e2, ω2, M02 and C with optional slope and t_mean"""
function model_2pl(t, P1, K1, e1, ω1, M1, P2, K2, e2, ω2, M2, C; slope=0.0, t_mean = 0.0)
    rv = calc_rv_keplerian(t-t_mean,P1,K1,e1,ω1,M1) + 
         calc_rv_keplerian(t-t_mean,P2,K2,e2,ω2,M2) + 
         C + slope * (t-t_mean)
end</code></pre>


<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>""" Convert vector of (P,K,h,k,ω+M0) to vector of (P, K, e, ω, M0) """
function PKhkωpM_to_PKeωM(x::Vector) 
    (P, K, h, k, ωpM) = x
    ω = atan(h,k)
    return [P, K, sqrt(h^2+k^2), ω, ωpM-ω]
end</code></pre>
